laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Increased to 13 nmol/L after 2 months of hCG therapy, then further increased to 12.5 nmol/L six weeks after discontinuing hCG. At six months after discontinuation, testosterone level was 7 nmol/L.

Increased to 3.9 IU/L six weeks after discontinuing hCG.
Unchanged during hCG therapy, then stable at 305 pg/mL six weeks after discontinuing hCG.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Sperm count was 0 initially. After hCG therapy, the sperm count was 89 million/mL and then 91.4 million/mL six weeks after discontinuing hCG.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Sperm count increased from 0 to 89 million/mL after 4 months of hCG therapy, then to 91.4 million/mL six weeks after discontinuation.
